    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Edge
    Represents a directed connection between a Place and a Transition.
    EdgeEmpty
    Represents an incoming edge that empties its origin Place upon activation.
    EdgeIn
    Represents an abstract incoming edge connecting a Place to a Transition.
    EdgeOut
    Represents an abstract outgoing edge connecting a Transition to a Place.
    EdgeZero
    Represents an incoming edge that activates only when its origin Place is empty.
    IPretriNet
    Defines the contract for a Petri net simulation.
    PetriNet
    Represents a Petri net system composed of places, transitions, and edges.
    Place
    Represents a place in a Petri net, used to store and manage tokens.
    Transition
    Represents a transition in a Petri net, responsible for moving tokens from input places to output places via edges.
    WeightedEdgeIn
    Represents an incoming edge with a specified weight.
    WeightedEdgeOut
    Represents an outgoing edge with a specified weight.
